        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 1 at 1:55PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 155 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Biscoe, or 7 miles southeast of Troy, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southern Pines, Pinehurst, Aberdeen, Biscoe, Hoffman, Whispering
Pines, Pinebluff, Foxfire, Candor and Taylortown.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
